Tor: The Second-Generation Onion Router, page 12

If an adversary can
run multiple ORs, and can persuade the directory servers that
those ORs are trustworthy and independent, then occasionally

another as the end of a circuit.  If an adversary controls
m > 1 of N nodes, he can correlate at most (m/N)^2 of the trafficâ€”
although an adversary could still attract a disproportionately
